### Topics

#### Part I - Mathematical Foundations

##### Chapter 1 - Introduction & Motivation

> The ==target audience== of the book **includes undergraduate university students**, **evening learners** and learners **participating in online machine learning courses**

- Reading ==strategies==/approaches
	- **Bottom-up**
		- learn definitions, ... & build from previous learning
		- "harder" ? to find motivation
	- **Top-down**
		- `through practical needs : the reader knows why to work on a particular concept (clear path)`
		- better for practitioners, goal-driven approach
		- downside : **potentially shaky foundations**

##### 11 - Density Estimation
- Gaussian Mixture Model (GMM)
- **11.3** - EM Algorithm (Dempster et al., 1977)
	- general iterative scheme for learning parameters in mixture models (GMM) (and more generally latent-variable models)
	- At each step Negative log-likelihood is decreased
	- E-step / M-step
- **11.5** - Further reading
	- Kernel density estimation
		- independently by Rosenblatt (1956) & Parzen (1962)
		- kernel function : non-negative function that integrate to 1
